<html><head><title> Multimedia</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center> Multimedia</h2><h3>Discover India CD-ROM for key stages 3 & 4 </h3><p><i>"This is a well-judged CD-ROM which will provide a valuable resource in any classroom where social issues are being raised, as well as in any geography room. It will also serve as an object lesson to some commercial publishers who would do well to follow ACTIONAID's attention to teaching and learning issues in the design of their CD-ROMs. Educational Value 91 per cent"</i><br> MacFormat magazine<p>Discover India CD-ROM offers an exciting new opportunity for pupils to acquire geographical knowledge and skills in the context of Indian life. The disk brings to the classroom an interactive mix of photographs, video clips, maps, animation, diagrams, satellite images and sound.<p>The disk's 13 modules cover National Curriculum geography, particularly the themes of weather and climate, population, settlement, migration, economic activities, development and environmental issues.<p><img src="hydro.jpg" width=267 height=200 border=1 align=left hspace=5 vspace=4><b>Modules include:</b><ul><li><b>Sampagni's Story</b> -  a video story of a child's life on Bangalore's streets.<li><b>The Hydrological Cycle</b> -  an animated hydrological cycle and choropleth maps illustrating temperature and rainfall.<li><b>Satellite Images</b>  - the cities of Bangalore and Bombay are investigated using remote-sensing images.</ul>The structure of the disk encourages enquiry-based work by individuals or small groups of pupils. Each module is designed to take 15 minutes to complete.The CD-ROM is dual platform, running on both multimedia PCs and Apple Macintosh computers.CD-ROM pack £55.00Minimum system requirements:Windowsª PCs: 33MHz 486, 8MB free RAM, VGA+ 256 colours, Windowsª 3.1, MPC soundcard.Macintosh¨ computers: LCIII, 4MB RAM, colour monitor (256 colours), System 7.0.<p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="resource.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="resource.html">Resources for teachers</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
