<html><head><title> Video packs</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center> Video packs</h2>These video packs are designed to provide additional information and new perspectives to enhance the study of localities. They are also ideal for cross-curricula work and general interest. The films have been specifically edited for the classroom, with clear discussion/learning outcomes. The support materials included with the videos further explore the issues and develop pupils' understanding.<p><hr><h3>Neighbours - the life and times of Yesudas Kemel</h3><p><i>Neighbours</i>  explores the life of a young boy and his family in Delhi and compares British and Indian cultures. It features community life, schools, public events and local industry.<p><i>This video won first prize in the 1993 Education Television Association Awards.</i><b>Video pack (30 mins) £25.00 </b><hr><h3>Working together - the people of Kanjikolly</h3><p>Produced to complement the <i>Chembakolli</i>  pack, this video features Kanjikolly, a community only three kilometres away from Chembakolli. The video explores the locality, its farming, education and health care by following the daily life of Padmini, Chandran and family.<p><i>This video won an Education Television Association award in 1995.</i><p><i>"A beautifully shot and sensitively edited evocation of life in a Southern Indian village. The video is not just part of a superb teaching package, it is also worth viewing as a video in its own right for anyone interested in other cultures and other ways of life - invaluable."</i><br>Roy Colquhoun, former chairman of the Education Television Association.<p><b>Video (2x 20 minute sessions) £25.00</b> <a name="kale"></a><hr><h3>Kale Nyabo - women farmers in Uganda </h3><p>Examines the working lives of women subsistence farmers in Uganda. Illustrates farming methods and the farming calendar in a tropical region.<p><b>Video pack (30 mins.) £25.00 </b><a name="bags"></a><hr><h3>Bags of money - handicraft producers in Kenya</h3><p>Examines the links between handicraft producers in Kenya and a UK importer. Reflects differences in business activity and trade at local and international levels.<p><b>Video pack (30 mins.) £25.00</b><p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="resource.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="resource.html">Resources for teachers</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
