<html><head><title> Resources for key stage 1 - new!</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center> Resources for key stage 1 - new!</h2><p>Similar resources to the Big Families Pack below will be available over the next 18 months on Peru and Bangladesh. If you would like further information on these please tick the box on the <b><a href="order.html">order form</a></b>. <p><h3>The Big Families Pack:The Mahama Family, Ghana </h3><p><i>"A visually stunning resource, which will give excellent support to teachers wanting an overseas locality study for key stage 1 children."</i><br>Julia Tanner, Senior Lecturer in Primary Education, Leeds Metropolitan University.<p>In response to requests from a large number of teachers, we have developed a new resource for key stage 1. The pack contains 10 A2 colour photo-boards, which give pupils an accessible introduction to a range of topics including family life, journeys, weather, water and food. Easy-to-reference information appears on the back of each photo-board, together with over 60 practical classroom activities. Photocopiable resources such as maps, activity sheets and a story are also included.   <p>The Mahama Family, Ghana will enable pupils to study "a locality either in the UK or overseas, in which the physical and/or human features contrast with those of the locality of the school," (Geography National Curriculum - key stage 1) and to draw comparisons between their own lives and that of the Mahama family. The pack is ideal both for geography and for cross-curricular work.<p><b>Photo-board pack £45</b><p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="resource.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="resource.html">Resources for teachers</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
