<html><head><title> Resources for key stage 2</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center> Resources for key stage 2</h2><p>Our range of photo and slide packs provide detailed case material on the daily lives of individuals, families and communities from areas of the world in which ACTIONAID has development programmes.<p>All the activities in the packs have been designed for group or pair work, with opportunities for teachers to set individual tasks or hold class discussions. The slide packs contain the same photos and information as the photopacks, but lend themselves to whole class presentation. <p>The packs enable pupils to develop their geographical skills and knowledge, as well as providing them with the opportunity to enhance their understanding of other people and cultures and the forces that affect all of our lives.<p>Although these resources are designed primarily for use at key stage 2, many teachers adapt the material and use it at key stages 1 and 3.<img src="27.jpg" align=right hspace=4 vspace=3 width=178 height=205 border=0><p>Typically, a photo or slide pack contains:<ul><li>30 colour photos (A4)<li>teachers' notes<li>background information on the country and locality<li>comparative statistics<li>matrices and calendars illustrating economic or social issues<li>maps of different scales</ul><hr><p><h3>Chereponi - Ghanaian rural life - new!  </h3><p>By studying the daily lives of one family through photographs, maps and information cards, pupils will build up an understanding of life in a remote area of Northern Ghana. There is a particular focus on change and the priorities people have for their future. The materials also provide opportunities for cross-curricular work, particularly in English and IT.<p><b>Colour photopack £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Pampagrande - a Peruvian village </h3><p>A locality case study of a Peruvian mountain village and its links with the local market. Focuses on the daily life of the Cubas Guevara family. <p><b>Colour photopack £15.00</b><br> <b>Slide pack £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Nairobi - Kenyan city life </h3> <p>Scenes, lifestyles and business activities, from Nairobi city centre to its urban slums, are explored. The two areas are linked by the work of the Obara family.<p><b>Colour photopack £15.00<br>Slide set £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Kapsokwony - rural Kenya </h3><p>Pupils examine the farming life of the Wanyoni family in western Kenya. A useful contrast to "Nairobi - Kenyan city life".<p><b>Colour photopack £15.00<br>Slide set £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Change in the Swat valley - Pakistan </h3> <p>Pupils investigate the social and economic changes taking place in a traditional rural community. Includes an activity on the physical changes to the Swat river valley. Complements the BBC "Landmarks" series on Pakistan.<p><b>Colour photopack £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Change in Pakistan </h3> <p>A set of four colourful A3 posters showing change in rural Pakistan. <p><b>Posters  £3.00 </b><hr><p><h3>Chembakolli - a village in India </h3> <p>Pupils use photos, picture cards and a large-scale map to find out about different aspects of the village and its inhabitants. <p><i><b>Chembakolli</b> received a 'Highly Commended' award from the Geographical Association: "sensitively written both for teachers who will be basing classwork on them and from the point of view of the villagers who are opening up their lives for examination."</i><p><b>Colour photopack £15.00<br>Slide set £15.00</b><hr><p><h3>Bangalore - Indian city life </h3><p>Lifestyles ranging from a middle- class family to homeless street children are examined through photos, sketch cards and an adventure booklet. <p><i><b>Bangalore</b> received a 'Highly Commended' award from the Geographical Association in 1993 for its "active, investigational and empathetic" approach. The GA citation states that "The pack provides entry to aspects of Indian life not generally available, selected to counter ethnic stereotypes, and giving plenty of ideas for successful teaching." </i><p><b>Colour photopack £15.00<br>Slide set £15.00</b><p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="resource.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="resource.html">Resources for teachers</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
