 <html><head><title> General Development Issues</title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600"><a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <ahref="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right><br><h2 align=center> General Development Issues</h2><p>All packs contain background information on the country or issue, teachers' notes and pupil activities.<hr><p><b>Roshunara's story</b> (suitable for key stages 2 & 3) - new edition<p>A week in the life of Roshunara and her family, who live on Bhola Island, Bangladesh. This resource actsas a stimulus to class discussion on daily life. Written in English and Bengali. <p><b>£3.00 </b><hr><p><b>Working with water</b> (suitable for key stages 2 & 3)<p>The story of Nuzrul's working week, as he plans and builds new tube wells with villagers on Bhola Island,Bangladesh.  <p><b>£3.00</b> <hr><p><b>Just add water</b> (suitable for key stages 2 & 3)<p>Information pack on water and sanitation, focusing on clean water and its importance. Illustrated byACTIONAID's overseas work. <p><b>£3.00</b><hr><p><b>Images of Africa and Britain</b> (suitable for all ages) <p>Shows a variety of landscapes and human activities from both Britain and Africa. Challenges pupils'expectations and stereotypical views of both areas.<p><b>Black and white photopack £5.00</b><hr><p><b>Which map projection?</b> (suitable for all ages)<p>Collection of world map outlines using the National Curriculum Equal Area Eckert IV projection. <p><b>Maps £1.00</b> <hr><p><b>Mullavassal</b><p>Pupils adopt the role of individual villagers living in an imaginaryIndian village. The villagers discuss their priorities for development. <p><b>Role play activity £2.00 </b><hr><p><b>Development without destruction</b><p>Snakes and Ladders board game raises awareness of environment, co-operation and development with more than one hundred stimulating questions. Available in English,French, German and Spanish <p><b>Game £3.00</b><p><hr><p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46 height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="resource.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46height=41hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li type=square><ahref="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">JoinACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="resource.html">Resources for teachers</a></b></font><br clear=all><p></body></html>
