<html>
<head>
<title> BANGLADESH</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<font face="arial, helvetica">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center> BANGLADESH</h2>


<p align=center><img src="../pix/bang.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=2 width=500 height=321 alt="Map of
Bangladesh">

<p><hr>

<b>Key National Statistics</b>

<p>Population	123 million

<p>Population growth rate	2.2% a year

<p>Under-5 child mortality rate	122
(deaths per 1,000 live births)

<p>Rural population with 	85%
access to safe water

<p>Adult literacy rate	37%
<hr>

<p><h3>Programme Overview </h3>

<p>ACTIONAID has been working in Bangladesh since 1983. Programmes are reaching more than 160,000
people in four development areas. 

<p>The focus of ACTIONAID's work in Bangladesh is on the formation of community groups called
shomitis. It is with these groups that the development initiatives are planned and managed, with an
emphasis on establishing savings and credit facilities and improving access to healthcare and
education
facilities.

<h3>Examples of ACTIONAID's work in Bangladesh </h3><b>ACTIONAID has:</b>

<p><ul><li>sunk 1,000 tube wells on Bhola Island to a depth of over 850 feet to provide clean water
for
more than 200,000 people.

<p><li>enabled more than 200,000 families to save and take small loans to stabilise household income,
set-up small businesses or, at times of crisis, purchase extra food or rebuild houses. 

<p><li>piloted a new approach to teaching adult literacy called Reflect (Regenerated Freirean
Literacy
through Empowering Community Techniques) where participants develop their own learning materials.
Group members construct maps, graphs and matrices  based on their own lives and through discussion
add key words. Experience has shown already that this technique is much more effective than teaching
adults by the same methods and with the materials used to teach children.

<p><li>helped more than 2000 households learn about improved health care practices, especially in
crucial
areas such as child care, sanitation and the treatment of common diseases.
</ul>
<hr>
<p><b><a href=".html">Islands in the storm</a></b>

<p>Find out about the people who live on Bangladesh's newly-formed islands. They are some of the
country's most vulnerable and ACTIONAID is the only charity working with them.

<p>
<b> <a href=".html">Bibi Nojupha stands up for her daughters' rights</a></b>

<p>Discover how ACTIONAID is promoting the rights of women on Bhola island.
</font>

<!--footer-->
<p><hr>
<p> <a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46
height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img
src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="index.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46
height=41
