<html>
<head>
<title> ETHIOPIA</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<font face="arial, helvetica">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center> ETHIOPIA</h2>
<p align=center>
<img src="../pix/ethiopia.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=2 width=436 height=272 alt="Map of Ethiopia">
</p>
<hr>
<b>Key National Statistics</b>

<p>Population	56.6 million

<p>Population growth rate	3% a year

<p>Under-five child mortality	204
(deaths per 1,000 live births)

<p>Rural population with 	19% 
access to safe water

<p>Adult literacy rate	32.7%
<br clear=left>
<p><hr>
<h3>Programme Overview </h3>

<p>ACTIONAID began working in Ethiopia in 1988. Its programmes are reaching more than 150,000 people
in
five development areas including urban projects in Addis Ababa. 

<p>In all areas, ACTIONAID's work begins with a survey, conducted with the full participation of the
community. These create a picture of the society and show the nature and extent of poverty. From the
results, ACTIONAID  and the community can plan health, education, water, agriculture and investment
programmes which best meet local needs. 

<p>Wherever possible ACTIONAID works by supporting local institutions such as health committees and
parent/teacher associations. By building on existing skills and resources, ACTIONAID enables the
community to take controls of its own development.

<h3>Example of ACTIONAID's work in Ethiopia</h3><b>ACTIONAID has:</b>

<p><ul><li>developed a water scheme in the Dalocha area, by capping springs, creating ponds and
digging
wells, that will eventually provide clean water for the entire 75,000 population of the area.

<p><li>upgraded and equipped a health centre in Dalocha, renovated three health clinics, constructed
16
rural health posts and, through training of traditional midwives and community health workers, helped
improve the provision of primary health care in the Dalocha area.

<p><li>established 20 new community literacy centres and improved school facilities in Koysha, so
helping
more than 4,000 children to gain an education.

<p><li>helped people in the slum district of Entoto, Addis Ababa, to improve the quality of their
lives
through developing better access to healthcare, income generation, and savings and credit schemes.

<p><li>supported many local non-governmental organisations in their work with the rural and urban
poor.
In Addis Ababa, ACTIONAID is collaborating with DAY (Development and You) to promote HIV/AIDS
awareness.
</ul>
<hr>

<p><b><a href=".html">Fighting the food gap</a></b>

<p>Find out about the Ethiopian communities who still have to negotiate the annual hungry season -
ACTIONAID is helping them through savings and credit schemes.

<p>
<b><a href=".html">Belayneh Adaye - farmer and 'bank manager'</a></b>

<p>Discover how Belayneh Adaye was able to buy his own ox, so saving himself the cost of hiring one
from
a richer farmer at the rate of two-thirds his crop.
</font>

<!--footer-->
<p><hr>
<p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46
height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img
src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="index.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><li type=square><b><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a></b> <li
type=square><b><a
href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">Join
ACTIONAID</a></b> <li type=square><b><a href="index.html">Country Programmes</a></b></font>
<br clear=all>
