<HEAD>
<Title>Kirkstall Valley campaign Letter</Title>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGColor="#FFFFFF" Text="#000000" Link="#0000FF" VLink="#FF00FF" ALink="#FF0000">

<IMG SRC="tliosml.gif" ALT="TLIO" WIDTH=29 HEIGHT=30 BORDER=0><H3>This is an update of the Kirkstall Valley Campaign rcd 25/1/97</H3>

<PRE>

NEWS FROM THE KIRKSTALL VALLEY CAMPAIGN

Residents of Kirkstall, Leeds are taking action this week in an attempt
to block plans for a large supermarket and retail complex in the
Kirkstall Valley.

A recent highly successful action in which supporters of Earth First!
occupied the Chairman of Morrisons PLC's office secured a meeting
between him and KVC, but the company failed to make any significant
concessions. Now, local residents are taking their own action which they
are inviting all organisations and individuals opposed to irresponsible
retail development to join.

On Thursday, January 30th at 4.00 pm there will be a "Mass Crossing" at
pedestrian controlled lights on the A65 (Kirkstall Road). This road is
already seriously overloaded at peak times, and the action could result
in "gridlock" right back to Leeds city centre. The proposed Morrison's
development would put between 5 and 10 thousand extra vehicles a day on
the route. People wishing to take part should meet at the Netto car park
on Kirkstall Road at 3.45. It is intended that the action will be over
by 5.00pm

The next day, Friday 31st Januiary, also at 4.00pm, we will demonstrate
outside Leeds Civic Hall where the LCC Highways. committee will be
meeting. This body has the power to prevent the Morrisons development by
refusing to approve the neccessary road works on the grounds that they
are not in the public interest. Meet for this action on the Civic Hall
steps at 3.45pm.

On the evening of Friday 31st there will be a benefit gig for the
Campaign. Local bands IZON PARADISE, THE TULIP LOUNGE and BINGO will be
playing at THE DUCHESS Vicar Lane, Leeds. Doors open 8.00pm, admission
three pounds.
----------------------------------------------------------

Thanks again for your support - I hope we will be linking to you from
our very own page soon.

Steve Kind
-- 
k  k         v       v        cccccc
k k           v     v         c
kkirkstall     valley         campaign
k k             v v           c
k  k             v            cccccc

</PRE>


