<head>
<title>TVE - Moving Pictures</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>The Moving Pictures Bulletin</h2>
<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>
A critical review of new environment and development films and videos, the Moving Pictures Bulletin
provides a unique information service to subscribers in both the developed and the developing world.
Published quarterly, the Bulletin has a global remit; to increase the flow of information between North and
South, East and West, on the latest productions dealing with environment, development, health,
human-rights and democratization issues, who distributes them, who is making them - and the context in
which they work. 
<p>

Over the years the Bulletin has developed a unique constituency among broadcasters, educationalists,
film-makers, festival organisers, and environment and development NGOs - growing from a simple listings
service to a specialist magazine, distributed in 120 countries. 
<p>

Each issue of the Bulletin is built around a specific theme, with contributions from writers, each experts in
their fields. Recent issues have featured: environmental programmes in North America, population, the
Indian environmental film and audio-visual outlook, indigenous peoples, the new challenges to
environmental film-making from the spread of cable and satellite broadcasting, the UN Conference on
Sustainable Development in Small Island Developing States (SIDS), the International Children's Day of
Broadcasting initiative, and the 1994 One World season to mark the International Conference on
Population and Development. 
<p>

The most recent issue of the Bulletin focuses on the issues surrounding the Fourth World Conference on
Women and has details of TVE's Women of the World series of programmes, as well as some of the best
films available elsewhere by and about women.

<p>

<pre>

</pre>
<ul type=square><li><b><a href="../info/distribution.html">TVE's Distribution and Information
Role</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../info/service.html">The Distribution Service</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="database.html">Moving Pictures Information Services</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../info/outreach.html">The OUTREACH service</a></b>
</ul></font>
