<head>
<title>TVE - Distribution and Information</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>TVE's Distribution and Information Role</h2>

<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>Helping to produce the programmes is only half the story. If
broadcasters in the South either don't know  what's available or don't have the hard currency to purchase
it, the programmes will never reach audiences in the developing world, and will be watched only in those
regions of the world where there is already a fairly high degree of environmental awareness. TVE's Moving
Pictures Service, launched in 1987, provided a way to reach out to audiences other commercial
distributors didn't bother with - particularly in the low income countries of the developing world.</font>
<p>

<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>The only editorially-independent service of its kind, Moving Pictures
combines its function as a clearinghouse for information about environmental films with a subsidised
distribution service for developing countries, offering a wide range of quality programmes on
environment, development, health and human rights issues for broadcast and non-broadcast use.
Moving Pictures is made up of four components: 
<p>

<ul type=square><li><b><a href="service.html">The Distribution Service</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../mp/home.html">The Moving Pictures Bulletin</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../mp/database.html">Moving Pictures Information Services</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="outreach.html">The OUTREACH service</a></b>
</ul></font>



<pre>
</pre>
<div align=right><a href="../index.html" target="_parent">TVE
Home
Page</div>
</body>
