<html>
<head>
<title>TVE - Distribution and Information</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>The Distribution Service</h2>
<font size=2 face=helvetica, arial>Each year, or as often as funding allows, TVE produces a catalogue listing
all the programmes it can make available to TV stations, NGOs and educational institutions in the South
as well as the CIS and Eastern Europe. Where TVE has the rights to distribute material to non-broadcast
users in the developed world, it charges commercial rates - allowing users in developing countries to
receive programmes on a subsidised basis. Catalogues are categorised thematically, as well as by genre
and geographical location. Southern broadcasters and NGOs worldwide select the programmes they want
and complete an order
form to TVE's Distribution Office in London, specifying the formats and languages they require. 
<p>

Language versioning is a critical element in ensuring Moving Pictures programmes are seen by the
maximum number of people worldwide. Wherever possible, TVE tries to provide programmes in the main
UN languages. Where TVE is unable to provide programmes in the language a Southern broadcaster
needs, it sends out an international master, with an English or French script, to enable  broadcasters to
dub  on their own language. 
<p>

Up to one third of the films are from programme-makers in the South or
North/South co-productions. Moving Pictures is the only distribution service promoting South-South
audio-visual exchange. Since it first started in 1987, the Moving Pictures service has distributed over
30,000 tapes to broadcasters, educational institutions and NGOs in developing countries and countries
with economies in transition.
<p>
<ul type=square><li><b><a href="distribution.html">TVE's Distribution and Information Role</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../mp/index.html">The Moving Pictures Bulletin</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../mp/database.html">Moving Pictures Information Services</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="outreach.html">The OUTREACH service</a></b>
</ul>
</font>
