<html>
<head>
<title>TVE - Distribution and Information</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>Moving Pictures Information Services</h2>
<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>
<b>The Moving Pictures Database</b><br>
Providing a complementary service to the Moving Pictures Bulletin, the Moving Pictures Database is a
directory of documentaries, dramas, children's programmes, animation and public service
announcements, in the areas of of environment, development, health and human-rights. All the films
reviewed for the Bulletin are added to  the database, together with further titles identified from film
festivals and distributors around the world and through exchanges with other databank operators. The
database contains details of approximately 1500 productions. 
<p>

The database is currently being updated to allow searches to be made by title, location, year, genre,
language, distributor and so on. On completion of this work, print-outs will be available free-of-charge to
users from developing countries: for film-makers or broadcast stations in the North, there is a charge of
US$30. The database is aimed at users like film-festival organisers, broadcast stations researching
environmental films, educational institutions and film-makers. 
<p>

<b>Round the World Crews</b><br>
The Round the World Crews database is part of TVE's policy of promoting film-making talent in the South.
It's a listing of over 300 film-making professionals - directors, producers, camera and sound technicians, as
well as fixers and post-production facilities in Africa, Asia, South America and the Caribbean and Eastern
Europe. The Service is primarily intended for broadcasters and independent production companies.
<p>

TVE has contacted all of the outfits listed and they have provided information on equipment, rates,
credits and references. A wide range of those listed produce work to what we believe is of international
broadcast quality and TVE has endeavoured as far as possible to check out the credentials for every
entry. However there will inevitably be differing views about 'professionalism'. In short Round the World
Crews should be seen as a reference directory and not necessarily as a TVE recommended list.
<p>
<ul type=square><li><b><a href="../info/distribution.html">TVE's Distribution and Information
Role</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../info/service.html">The Distribution Service</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="index.html">The Moving Pictures Bulletin</a></b><br>
<li><b><a href="../info/outreach.html">The OUTREACH service</a></b>
</ul>

</font>
