<TITLE>ACP SECRETARIAT</TITLE>
</HEADER>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<pre>

</pre><center><A HREF="index.html"><img src="images/acp.jpg"></A></center>
<P>
<H4 align=center>General Secretariat of the Africa, Caribbean and Pacific Group of States<br>
Secr&#233;tariat g&#233;n&#233;ral du groupe des Etats d'Afrique, des Cara&#239;bes, et du Pacifique</H4>

<center>Mr Carl GREENIDGE</a><br>CURRICULUM VITAE, December 1996</center>
<hr>
<IMG align=left SRC="images/carlgr.gif">Carl B. GREENIDGE, a well known Caribbean economist, is currently Deputy Secretary General of the General Secretariat of the African, Caribbean and Pacific (ACP) Group of States.  He has worked in the Caribbean, Africa and the UK in the field of economics both at a technical and policy-making level.  In the latter capacity, Minister of Finance (and initially Planning and Trade), he was one of the longest serving Ministers of Finance in the Commonwealth.
<p>
Mr GREENIDGE has held a variety of University teaching and research posts and has published several refereed articles on economics.  He has had a long association with the EEC having been the ACP Ministerial Spokesman on Trade and Commodity Protocols during the negotiation of the Lom&#233; III Convention and subsequently, President of the ACP-EEC Joint Council of Ministers in which capacity he launched the 1st Protocol of Lom&#233; IV.
<p>
He is Vice-Chairman of the Board of the ECDPM in Maastricht and a member of the Advisory Boards of the Regulatory Policy Institute and the Regulatory Policy Centre Hartford College, University of Oxford in the UK.
<p>
<center><h4><a href="index.html">La page ACP</a> / <a href="index.html">ACP Home Page</a></h4></center>
<p>
