<Title>TLIO - Pure Genius - Bust card</Title>
<META NAME="author" CONTENT="Steve Jones stevej@dircon.co.uk">
<META NAME="description" CONTENT="The Land Is Ours: a landrights campaign based in Britain, this page , a Bust Card handed out at the begining of the Pure Genius!! occupation.">
</Head>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FFFF00">

<CENTER>
<H1><B>THE LAND IS OURS</B></H1>
<H3><I>a landrights campaign for Britain</I></H3>
<IMG SRC="tlio.gif" ALT="TLIO" WIDTH=182 HEIGHT=187 BORDER=0>
</CENTER>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="puregen2.jpg" ALT="Pure Genius!!" WIDTH=390 HEIGHT=44 BORDER=0>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+2><I>ECO VILLAGE WANDSWORTH</I></FONT>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><B>This is a representation of the 'Bust-card' handed out on the occupation.</B></CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER><TABLE CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=0 WIDTH=600 BORDER=0 BGCOLOR="#1AACB0">

<CAPTION>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><b>LEGAL INFORMATION</b></FONT>
<BR>
<B>For this demonstration</B>
</CAPTION>

<TR>
<TD>


* IF YOU ARE ARRESTED: 
<P>
*   Shout out your name - so we can locate you.  
<BR>
*   Note the numbers of the arresting officer(s).
<P>
*   AT THE POLICE STATION YOU STILL HAVE A RIGHT:
<P>
*   To know why you have been arrested, so ask.  
<P>
*   To remain silent.  There is NO requirement to talk to the police.  We strongly advise you to:
<OL>
<LI>make "NO COMMENT" to all questions,  
<LI>don't write a statement, 
<LI>don't sign a statement written by the police, and 
<LI>don't sign any police notebook until you have seen a solicitor recommended by us.  
</OL>

The Criminal Justice Act HAS NOT got rid of the right to silence.  It's being used to intimidate us.   
<P>
*   You are obliged, however, to give the police a name & address.  You don't have to give your date of birth, but it may delay your release. 
<P>
*   You have the right to a solicitor of your choice.
<P>
<b>IF YOU ARE ARRESTED PHONE US TO ARRANGE A SOLICITOR FOR YOU IMMEDIATELY, ON:  XXXX - XXX XXXX</b>
<P>
*   Once you are charged you should be released.  If not ask why.  
<P>
*   They can fingerprint & photograph you if you are charged.  
<P>
*   If the police assault you go to casualty immediately or call us for a sympathetic doctor and get your injuries recorded.
<P>
DON'T TALK - DON'T PANIC - YOU'LL SOON BE OUT
<P>
LEGAL OBSERVERS ARE WEARING BRIGHT ORANGE BIBS.  Their role is to monitor police (mis) behaviour and to assist anyone arrested or injured by gathering information.  Please cooperate with them  - your assistance may help save a protester from imprisonment.  On the demo - look after each other.  Try to make sure you are with people who know your name and will look out for you.  
<P>
*   IF YOU WITNESS AN ARREST:
<P>
*   Write down the name of the arrested person 
<P>
*   Write down the number of the arresting officer(s)
<P>
*   Get this information and your own name & phone number to a legal observer (LO)
<P>
*   If you witness an arrest or you want information about somebody who may have been arrested - CALL US ON 0171-837-6687.  Our office will be open all weekend if there are arrests.
<P>
*   IF YOU ARE INJURED OR WITNESS AN INJURY: 
<P>
*   Get emergency medical treatment from the ambulance service.  Contact LDMG Independent doctors can examine and photograph injuries.  This may help in the event of legal action against you or the police.
<P>
*   The LEGAL DEFENCE & MONITORING GROUP will give unconditional support to any person arrested on this demo.  We need affiliations & donations and people to help.  We urge you to get involved.  Contact us at:  B.M. BOX HAVEN, LONDON, WCIX 3NN OR PHONE 0171-837-6687.    

</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>
</CENTER>

