>         <P>THURSDAY 5 SEPTEMBER</P>                  <P>Hans-Heino Kopietz, independent security consultant and         expert on Kurdistan      </TD><TD>         <P>1900      </TD><TD>         <P>8 pm      </TD><TD>         <P>3 pm      </TD><TD>         <P>12 noon      </TD><TD>         <P>3 am Fri      </TD><TD>         <P>5 am Fri      </TD></TR>   <TR>      <TD COLSPAN=10>         <P>During the sessions, please put your questions by sending         a private message to the host of the session, using the         command /msg PaulEedle or /msg JohnWest. For full details,         please see the note on chat         <A HREF="#etiquette">etiquette</A> below.      </TD></TR></TABLE></P><P><FONT SIZE=4>OutThere's talk and interviews use the Internet RelayChat system. If you already know how</FONT> <FONT SIZE=4>to use IRC,connect your chat client to neato.ca.us.another.org port 6667 channel#OutThere. If you're new to Internet Relay Chat, you'll need to setup in advance:</FONT></P><P><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1 WIDTH="100%">   <TR>      <TD align=CENTER>         <P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="#windows">Windows         users</A></FONT>      </TD><TD align=CENTER>         <P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="#macintosh">Macintosh         users</A></FONT>      </TD></TR></TABLE></P><H2><HR><A NAME="windows"></A><FONT SIZE=4>Windows setup</FONT></H2><P>These instructions are based on the Windows 95 version of mIRC.The Windows 3.x version may appear slightly different but thecommands to enter are the same.</P><UL>   <LI><A HREF="http://www.mirc.co.uk/get.html">Download and install   the mIRC client.</A>      <LI>Open your link to the Internet.      <LI>Open the mIRC application. When the "about mIRC" window   appears, close it.      <LI>When a second window opens, click the "Add" button in the   right-hand corner.      <LI>Enter the following settings:      <UL>      <LI>Description: Another.Net            <LI>IRC server: neato.ca.us.another.net            <LI>Port: 6667            <LI>Real Name: Please enter your full name as a courtesy to our      interviewees, so they know who is questioning them.            <LI>Email: Please enter your email address so we can alert you      to future live events.            <LI>Nickname: Up to 9 characters without any spaces. Please use      your real name and the first letters of your family name.            <LI>Alternative: (leave blank)   </UL>      <LI>Click OK      <LI>Double-click "Another.Net" in the list of servers. After a few   seconds, the screen will tell you that you are connected to   AnotherNet.      <LI>Click "Join" in the "Commands" pull-down menu. Enter   "OutThere" in the dialogue box. The screen will tell you that you   have joined the OutThere channel.</UL><P><FONT SIZE=4>For any questions on the software, see</FONT><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="http://www.mirc.co.uk">mIRC's HomePage.</A></FONT></P><UL>   <FONT SIZE=4>&nbsp;</FONT></UL><H2><FONT SIZE=4><HR><A NAME="macintosh"></A>Macintosh setup</FONT></H2><UL>   <LI><A HREF="http://www.globalchat.com/download.html">Download and   install the Global Chat client.</A>      <LI>Open your link to the Internet.      <LI>Open the Global Chat application and select the command "New"   from the File Menu. A dialogue box will open.      <LI>Click the button for "More Detail" to expand the dialogue box.      <LI>Enter the following settings:      <UL>      <LI>Connect to: Global Stage            <LI>Nickname: Up to 9 characters without any spaces. Please use      your real name and the first letters of your family name.            <LI>Connection label: Global Stage            <LI>Server name or IP: neato.ca.us.another.net            <LI>Port number: 6667            <LI>Initial Channel: OutThere            <LI>Channel password: (leave blank)            <LI>Full name: Please enter your full name as a courtesy to our      interviewees, so they know who is questioning them.            <LI>Email address: Please enter your email address so we can      alert you to future live events.            <LI>Home page: Enter the URL of your home page if you have one.      </UL>      <LI>Click the "Save and Connect" button. After a few seconds, the   main Global Chat screen will appear and text in the largest window   will tell you you are connected to AnotherNet and have joined the   OutThere channel.</UL><P><FONT SIZE=4>For any questions on the software, Global Chat offersa full</FONT><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="http://www.globalchat.com/help/index.html">helpguide.</A></FONT></P><P><FONT SIZE=4><HR>If you have difficulty connecting to theneato.ca.us.another.org server, try one of the other servers on theAnotherNet IRC network:</FONT></P><UL>   <LI><FONT SIZE=4>dragon.ne.us.another.net</FONT>      <LI><FONT SIZE=4>sunrise.ca.us.another.net </FONT>      <LI><FONT SIZE=4>together.vt.us.another.net </FONT></UL><P><FONT SIZE=4>Full details of AnotherNet are on its</FONT><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="http://www.another.org">homepage.</A></FONT></P><P>&nbsp;</P><H1><A NAME="etiquette"></A><HR>Interview etiquette</H1><P>Please log onto the talk or the interviews using your real firstname and the first letters of your family name as your Nickname, andenter your real name and e-mail address in your chat client so thatwe know who you are. We think it is a courtesy to interviewees thatthey should know who is asking them questions.</P><P>During the interviews, please route your questions to the gueststhrough the host. Send your question in a private message to theinterview host using the "to:" dialogue box in the bottom right handcorner of Global Chat or the /msg command on any chat client. Toprevent everybody speaking at once, the interview channel is"moderated", which means people can only speak publicly if invited todo so by the host.</P><P>The hosts will be either John West - nickname JohnWest on thesystem - or Paul Eedle - nickname PaulEedle.</P><P>There is a limit on how many questions we can take from the floorduring the sessions, so you might like to send a question in advanceby<A HREF="MAILTO:75714.1042@compuserve.com, johnwest@logos.cy.net">e-mail.</A></P><P>That's it! Please join in and afterwards<A HREF="mailto:75714.1042@compuserve.com, johnwest@logos.cy.net">letus know what you think.</A></P><P><HR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="ot_pix/ot_logo.gif"ALT="OutThere logo" WIDTH=83 HEIGHT=30 ALIGN=middle></A>Back to<A HREF="index.html">OutThere home page</A> ... OR ... Back to<A HREF="kurds2.html">'Kurds use crisis'</A></P><P>&nbsp;</P><P>&nbsp;</P><UL>   &nbsp;      <P>&nbsp;</P></UL></BODY></HTML>
