</pre>
<H2>ACP-EU Institutions</H2>
<UL>
<LI><a href="../ja_gb.htm">ACP-EU Joint Assembly</a>
<LI>ACP-EU Council of Ministers
<LI>ACP-EU Committee of Ambassadors
<LI><a href="../cdi/cdi.htm">Centre for the Development of Industry</a><ul><font size=3><I>CDI is financed by the European Development Fund (EDF) to encourage and support the creation, expansion and restructuring of industrial companies (mainly in manufacturing and agro-industry) in ACP countries. It promotes partnerships between ACP and European companies, These may take
various forms: financial, technical or commercial partnership, management contract, licensing or franchise agreement, subcontract, etc.</I></font></ul>
<LI><A HREF="../cta/cta.htm">Techical Centre for Agricultural and Rural Cooperation (CTA)</a><ul><font size=3><I>CTA develops and provides services which improve the access of ACP countries to information on agricultural and rural development, and it strengthens the capacity of ACP countries to produce, acquire, exchange and utilise information in these areas. It does this by strengthening information centres, promoting contact and exchange of experience among CTA's partners, and by providing information on demand.</I></font></ul> 

<li><A HREF="../news/joint_gb.htm">News</a>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>
