<H1>OutThere logoOutThere hairline</H1>

<H1>Northern Ireland: Is peace dead?<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=1
WIDTH="100%">
   <TR>
      <TD VALIGN=top COLSPAN=8>
         <P>Miltown
      </TD><TD COLSPAN=12>
         <P>By JOHN WEST</P>
         
         <P>DERRY/LONDONDERRY, AUGUST 9 - This is a dangerous weekend
         for the failing peace process in Northern Ireland. Long
         negotiations have failed to defuse a crisis over Saturday's
         planned march by the Apprentice Boys Association, which
         commemorates a crucial victory by Protestant colonists over
         Irish Catholics 300 years ago. Catholics have decided to
         hold their own march on Friday night.
         <A HREF="ot_danger.html">Full story.</A></P>
         
         <P>The Irish perspective:
         <A HREF="http://www.wrn.org/stations/rte.html">latest radio
         news from RTE</A></P>
         
         <P><B><FONT SIZE=2>Left:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2>
         </FONT><B><FONT SIZE=2>Miltown cemetery in
         Belfast</FONT></B>
      </TD></TR>
</TABLE></H1>

<P><HR><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="ot_live.html">On the streets after the
Apprentice Boys' march</A></FONT><FONT SIZE=4> - Edited transcript of
live chat with correspondent John West and Nationalists in the centre
of Londonderry on Saturday 10 August.</FONT></P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Unionist values must be accommodated -
</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=4>Alex Attwood, Social Democratic and Labour
Party member of Belfast City Council, argues for a negotiated peace
in Northern Ireland. Edited transcript of
</FONT><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="ot_attwood.html">OutThere
interview</A></FONT><FONT SIZE=4> conducted live on the Net on Sunday
11 August.</FONT></P>

<P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Nationalists talk at us and about us but not to
us</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=4> - Ken Maginnis, Ulster Unionist MP for
Fermanagh and South Tyrone, blames Nationalists for lack of progress
towards peace. Edited transcript of
</FONT><FONT SIZE=4><A HREF="ot_maginnis.html">OutThere
interview</A></FONT><FONT SIZE=4> conducted live on the Net on Sunday
11 August.</FONT></P>

<P><B><A HREF="ot_debate.html">How to join</A> future live events...
Please also look at our interview
<A HREF="ot_debate.html#etiquette">etiquette.</A></B></P>

<P><B><HR></B></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>Reporting by John West. Production by Paul Eedle.
</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>About <A HREF="ot_info.html">OutThere.</A></P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>Please
<A HREF="mailto:75714.1042@compuserve.com, johnwest@logos.cy.net">tell
us what you think</A> of OutThere. What issues and events would you
like us to cover?</P>

