<TITLE>PAF PROACTIVE FILE 27</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.04z">
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<P>
<CENTER><IMG align=middle src="../euforic/images/eustep.jpg"></CENTER>
<H3><CENTER>PAF PROACTIVE FILE<BR>
Regular News Update From Eurostep No. 27 Friday 14 November 1996</CENTER>
</H3>
<H4><CENTER>EUROSTEP<BR>
115 Rue St&eacute;vin, B-1000 Brussels, Belgium<BR>
Tel.: (32)-2-2311659 / Fax: (32)-2-2303780<BR>
E-mail: <A href="mailto:eurostep@knooppunt.be">eurostep@knooppunt.be</A></CENTER>
</H4>
<HR>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>1. EUROPEAN PARLIAMENT CALLS FOR MULTINATIONAL
FORCE</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Members of the European Parliament on Wednesday 13
November approved of a resolution calling for the creation of
humanitarian corridors and the immediate set up of a multinational
force to ensure the safe passage of aid. The MEPS want an embargo
of arms exports to the region and a general disarmament of the
civilian population in the region.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Mr. Jean-Fran&ccedil;ois Hory of the Radical party
stated that the mandate of the multinational force should not
allow it to strengthen the Zairian regime and protect its corrupt
army who are prone to pillaging and looting. </FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>EC Commissioner for Humanitarian Relief Emma Bonino
commended Europe on speaking with a single voice on the issue
stating, &quot;those preventing the sending of a force are on
the other side of the Atlantic.&quot; But she noted that without
a military force ,total unanimity could not save lives. According
to Mrs Bonino the multinational force should be given the mandate
to deliver basic goods protect the refugees and humanitarian material
and personnel, and facilitate the voluntary return of refugees.
On the urgency of the situation Mrs Bonino stated that &quot;If
a decision is not taken immediately, the force that will end up
on location will have nothing else to do bury the dead. .... And
what anger, frustration and shame we shall have to bear.&quot;
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The European Parliamentarians paid tribute to Mrs
Bonino's efforts to resolve the crisis while acknowledging that
the international community would have to bear some responsibility
for the crisis. Mrs Francisca Sauquilo a Spanish socialist wondered
why the EU was not using its capacity to act but rather trailing
the United States and Canada.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>2.ACP EU REPRESENTATIVES ADOPT DECLARATION TO
REFORM DEVELOPMENT COOPERATION <BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>ACP and EU representatives last week adopted a final
declaration on the future of ACP-EU cooperation following their
20th annual meeting organised by the Economic and Social Committee.
The representatives recognised the need to adapt cooperation to
globalisation of the economy and to foster conditions for a new
sustainable convention that will ensure economic growth, prevent
crisis and upgrade the wellbeing of the populations. </FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>The main principles proposed for the new Lom&eacute;
Convention after the year 200 are given below:</FONT>
<OL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>The new convention aims to a) preserve the principles
of equality and the partnership of the lom&eacute; Convention;
b) promote good administration , human rights democracy and the
state of law; c) take in account the Maastricht Treaty on European
development policies, as well as the Uruguay round d) adopt a
more flexible approach to development cooperation reflecting the
different social and economic development of the ACP states. 
<BR>
</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2>In order to reach theses aims the declaration
calls for an increase in the active participation of economic
and social partners<BR>
</FONT>
</OL>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>3. ANTI DISCRIMINATION CLAUSE IN THE TREATY IS
WRLCOMED<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Anti discrimination and anti-racist representatives
from organizations in EU Member states, Starting Line, welcomed
the &ccedil;&ccedil;&agrave;!&ccedil; last week with the Irish
prseidency in Dublin. Irish Minister for Equality, Mr. Mervyn
Taylor informed the meeting of the Presidents proposal to include
the anti-discrimination clause. The Starting Line representatives
recalled their own proposal backed by almost 300 Union organizations
as well as the Consultative Commission on Racism and Xenophobia,
Kahn Commission. The proposals will allow the EU to adopt legal
and other measures to by a qualified majority too early to determine
what kind of clause would be acceptable to all member states.</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2>4.PARLIAMENT CALLS ON EU TO ACT COHERENTLY AT
SINGAPORE WTO MINISTERIAL MEETING AND SUPPORTS COMMISION REFORM
PROPOSAL ON ARTICLE 113<BR>
</FONT></B>
<HR>
