<html>
<head>
<title>CASE FOR AID</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#000000" text="#ffffff">
</a><br clear=all><br>
<h6>The material that follows has been provided by  <a href="oxfam.html">OXFAM UK&I</a></h6><hr><p>

<center><font size=7>the case for AID</font></center>
<h4 align=center>A MANIFESTO</h4>


Against a background of unprecedented decline in aid budgets around the world, this manifesto renews the vision of overseas aid in the 1990s.<p>

At a time of growing inequality both within and between countries, it argues that the moral case for aid is stronger than ever before. But it also illustrates why the provision of aid to the poorest is ultimately in all our interests.<p>


<br>

The message of this manifesto is that:<ul>
<li><b><a href="works.html">Aid works</a></b> - At the right levels, and properly targeted, aid can work. It can help people who are not reached by other capital flows.<p>

<li><b><a href="spend.html">Spend now, save later</a></b> - Aid can promote long-term development and growth: by spending now, we can save lives and resources, and protect the environment.<p>

<li><b><a href="handup.html">Aid is a hand-up, not a hand-out</a></b> - It is a sound investment which helps people to help themselves.<p>

<li><b><a href="interests.html">Aid is in all our interests</a></b> - It can help to prevent conflict and tackle the problems of drug trafficking, environmental degradation, migration and epidemics that are linked to poverty.<p>

<hr width=71%><p>

<li><b><a href="summary.html">Summary</a>
<li><a href="summary.html#recommendations">Recommendations</a>
<li><a href="imperative.html">The New Moral Imperative</a>
<li><a href="notes.html">Notes</a></b><p>
</ul><hr width=71%><p>

<center><h3><a href="../../vso/aidcounts.html">VSO launches Aid Counts campaign</a></h3></center>
 Since 1979, the British government has been cutting aid. In last November's budget, aid was slashed by a further 5.4%. <a href="../../vso/aidcounts_form.html">Join VSO's campaign to send 10,000 messages</a> to the British government to show that people like you believe AID COUNTS. <p>
<hr><p>

<font size=2><center>This manifesto has been produced by the following organisations:<br>
All members of this group support the recommendations in this document, although the text does not necessarily reflect the policy of any individual organisation.</font></i><p>

<a href="../../actionaid/index.html"></a>
