<html><head><title>So you want to work overseas with VSO? </title><!!keys: ></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff"><hr><h2>Yes, VSO is not a relief agency sending emergency supplies.</h2>VSO aims to work in long term sustainable development. Most volunteers go overseas for two years. Teaching and training people in developing countries is what VSO does and this takes time. The need is not simply for another 'pair of hands'.  In reality, without a skill to offer you are just another mouth to feed. Volunteers always use the skills they are trained in. You have to be able to contribute positively.  <hr><center><TABLE BORDER=1><TR><TH><a href="page7.html">Continue</a></TH><TH><a href="rio.html">RIO Home Page</a></TH><TH><a href="../index.html">VSO Home Page</a></TH></TR></TABLE></center></body></html>
